Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.55,0:00:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The most precious moment in life is the time of decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.37,0:00:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace, but it also leaves us with many lessons to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.27,0:00:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Ketsudan = (decision)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.27,0:00:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Use your wisdom Use your head Keep thinking if you're a man
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.13,0:00:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you cry or laugh, it depends on your decision
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.20,0:01:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be arrogant even if you win Don't cry even if you lose
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.06,0:01:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Man does not show tears
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.58,0:01:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Tatsunoko Production
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.61,0:01:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,After a successful surprise attack on Hawaii, the Japanese army, which began the Pacific War,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.57,0:02:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,advanced to Hong Kong, the Malay Peninsula, the Philippines, Celebes, Borneo, etc. Next were the Java islands.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.92,0:02:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The main purpose of Operation Java was to acquire abundant oil resources and to create a line of defense connecting the islands of Sumatra and Java.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.88,0:02:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time, Java was the Dutch East Indies. It is Indonesia now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.40,0:02:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,First, paratroopers of the Japanese Army descended to Palembang Airfield on Sumatra Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.51,0:02:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Battle of Java (Episode Nine)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.40,0:02:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The General Staff saw the capture of Java as the most difficult of the Southern operations,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.23,0:02:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and the oil fields were likely to be destroyed before the Japanese occupied them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.61,0:03:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The refinery and airfield were occupied by the paratroopers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.81,0:04:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,In this way, the Japanese army conquered Sumatra, and started the siege of Java.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.40,0:04:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,On February 27th, 40,000 members of the 16th Army, commanded by Lieutenant General Imamura, began their march on Java.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.19,0:04:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,> The Allied commander of Java Island was Lieutenant General Hein ter Poorten of the Netherlands.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.92,0:04:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The Allied forces that protected Java numbered 80,000 in total, from the Netherlands, Britain, the US, Australia,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.78,0:05:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and local soldiers. In other words, it was twice the strength of the Japanese army.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.74,0:05:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But the Dutch Allied forces could convert as many as 50 million local civilians into soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.64,0:05:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Already in Indonesia, under the leadership of Soekarno and Hatta, there was a thriving national independence movement to resist Dutch rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.99,0:05:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Knowing the approach of the Japanese force the Dutch Allied fleet under the command of Major General Dolman, set sail,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.78,0:05:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,but was immediately destroyed by the Japanese fleet in the Battle of the Java Sea off Slavaya.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.47,0:06:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,However, torpedoes also hit four Japanese ships watching this battle in Bantam Bay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.57,0:06:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Ironically, a friendly torpedo passed under a US cruiser to hit one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.78,0:06:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,They also hit Sakuramaru, the ship on which Commander Imamura of the 16th Army was on.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.43,0:06:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Imamura unexpectedly had to swim in the warm southern sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.81,0:07:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the General changed ships, and on March 1st, the Japanese army made every effort to begin landing on Java Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.05,0:07:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The main force of the 16th Army was divided into three parts and made good progress, all aiming to take Bandung.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.61,0:08:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,> The entire army has landed successfully. > How is the battle going?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.68,0:08:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,> Very well. No, it's just too good.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.23,0:08:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,> Both the enemy and their allies, want to end this battle with minimal damage. > Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.30,0:08:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,> This is not a battle of attrition. I want to force the other party to surrender, with as little damage as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.09,0:08:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,> Well, it's still a long way off.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.57,0:08:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,> Commander Ter Poorten was frustrated because he did not know the location of the Japanese army.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.81,0:08:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,> He is currently reviewing the situation of each district. The Japanese army has 30,000 to 40,000 troops.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.19,0:08:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,> Isn't it possible to get reliable information quickly?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.68,0:09:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,> Since we are an Allied Forces of four countries, it takes time to contact each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.54,0:09:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,> I want more accurate information.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.54,0:09:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,> What are the natives doing? Let's use them to gather reliable information.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.57,0:09:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,> Actually... > What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.05,0:09:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,> The number of Japanese troops that landed is about 50,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.50,0:09:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,> 50,000?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.33,0:09:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,> It seems that the Japanese army in Bandam Bay is 80,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.78,0:09:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,> 80,000!?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.78,0:10:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,> What, 200,000!?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.02,0:10:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,> Comprehensive information from the field shows that the Japanese army has at least 200,000 troops.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.47,0:10:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Information about the Japanese Army was thus extremely exaggerated by the local residents and passed on to the Dutch side,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.88,0:10:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was believed that the 16th Army had 200,000 troops until the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.19,0:10:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,> The Dutch army was confused by the information from the locals, so they made efforts to collect information.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.19,0:10:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet the indigenous peoples’ national independence movement favored tie Japanese military in all respects.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.85,0:11:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,> How is the Japanese army moving? Give me reliable information.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.78,0:11:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,> What? Want to know the movement of the Japanese army? That's impossible. The newspaper hasn't been distributed yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.02,0:11:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,> The enemy has weekly counter-attacked in various places.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.43,0:11:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,> The less resistance, the less damage to our allies.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.68,0:12:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,> Is that a new tank?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.54,0:12:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,> As of March 3rd, there was a report that the Japanese army had not yet landed on Java Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.50,0:12:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What a load of bull!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.37,0:12:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,> It's a Japanese tank.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.30,0:12:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,> Lieutenant General Imamura made a propaganda broadcast in order to lessen the fighting spirit of the Dutch army.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.16,0:13:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese army in Burma seems to have landed in Rangoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.68,0:13:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,> What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.26,0:13:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,> It seems that the Churchill Cabinet in England has taken responsibility for the fall of Singapore and has resigned altogether.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.26,0:13:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,> The broadcast pleased the natives, and the Japanese army advanced with the support of the locals.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.95,0:14:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,> However, as they approached Bandung, the resistance of the Dutch Allied Forces became fierce.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.12,0:15:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,> At this time, the Japanese army's advance was stagnating.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.74,0:15:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,On March 7th, a unit of more than 700 soldiers was formed. They planned to rush into the suburbs of Bandung.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.43,0:15:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,> If the Indonesians are so hostile, then guerrilla warfare is almost inevitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.95,0:15:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if my Dutch troops surrender, the troops of each country may ignore my ceasefire order.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.57,0:16:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,> Commander. As long as your Dutch soldiers fight we, the British and the Australians, will continue to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.85,0:16:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,> The determined words of the British, Australian commanders, and Major General Sitwell were all empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.30,0:17:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,> Major General Pessman, who defends the northern central region of Bandung, surrendered quickly within a few hours of the start of the Japanese attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.40,0:17:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,> Certainly, it is a messenger from Major General Pessman, commander of the North Central Region?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.85,0:17:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,> He is definitely a messenger.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.78,0:17:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,> Even though they resisted fiercely. Strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.61,0:17:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,> I think the enemy is setting a trap. At this time, the city should be thoroughly destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.50,0:17:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,> It is unavoidable to burn it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.95,0:17:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,> Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.47,0:17:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,> I understand that feeling. The damage to the allies are increasing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.78,0:17:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,> The enemy resists, but does not try to leave the city. Perhaps they will build a defensive position and fight a decisive battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.30,0:17:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,> However, there will be many casualties to the local people.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.47,0:18:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,> No, we can evict them as much as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.26,0:18:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, please make a decision. Time is running out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.37,0:18:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,> Even if the allies are damaged, the local people must be protected Scorched earth operations are not allowed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.81,0:18:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,If you damage them here, you will lose their cooperation during the occupation. We did not come to fight the locals.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.09,0:18:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,> Yes > Good. Let him negotiate.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.43,0:18:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,> A Japanese military officer disguised as a local citizen with an interpreter had already infiltrated Bandung as a conspirator and was on standby.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.61,0:18:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,However, on March 7th, before the Japanese troops rushed into Rembang, he immediately departed upon receiving an order from his military commander.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.61,0:19:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,> I am the Japanese Lieutenant General Yanagikawa, and I want to meet the Commander of the Allied Forces of Java: Lieutenant General Tempur.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.19,0:19:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.43,0:19:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,> The Japanese army has completely taken the Java Island. The city of Bandung has also been sieged.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.23,0:19:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Further useless resistance should be stopped immediately and we recommend your surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.57,0:21:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,> On March 8th, the Dutch army finally abandoned the fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.54,0:21:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bandung District Defense Commander, Major General Pessman, Governor Chalder, Lieutenant General Telpurten,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.37,0:21:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and Major General Pakkas, Chief of Staff of the Army, met with Commander Imamura.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.09,0:21:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,> The situation near Bandung is terrible. I don't want to subject the citizens to any more misery.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.50,0:21:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to surrender Bandung.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.68,0:21:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,> The surrender of Bandung is not the issue. The Japanese military demands a total unconditional surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.05,0:22:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,> The Bandung Broadcasting Station finally broadcast a stop order to the entire army.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.88,0:22:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, the capture of Java, which was expected to be the most difficult of the Southern Operations,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.71,0:22:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,was successful with unexpectedly small casualties, due to careful planning and the cooperation of the local people.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.33,0:23:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,>On March 10th, the 16th Army unit, under the command of Lieutenant General Imamura, entered Bandung.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.40,0:23:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Operation Java is said to have been the only operation that received the welcome support of the local residents during the Pacific War and achieved the desired results.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.85,0:23:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be said that it was compassion that led Commander Lieutenant General Imamura
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.71,0:23:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to protect the indigenous people and reject scorched earth tactics.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.29,0:24:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace, but it also leaves us with many lessons to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.92,0:24:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If you are a man, test your strength If you are a man, burn your hope
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.44,0:24:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,If you area man, don't let yourself down
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.20,0:25:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I and you are men and men bleed the same bright red blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.51,0:25:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Tatsunoko Production
